</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugiljabet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giljabet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Barbie doll<BR><font color=#ff0000>lover</font></span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 8:27:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1466.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsdown.gif" align=absmiddle>  This is good...</span><hr size=1> ...I'll mostly leave it to the other classes to say what they will about their own class nerfs.<br>
<br>
But the &quot;best defensive class&quot; comment about the monk is just hilarious. Or do EQ developers only play characters that have Vex Thal-grade equipment on them? They probably tank better than warriors that are tanking Vindi or whatever - But then again They Should! Since when did a monk tank anything for his guild? Hell, if you run out of warriors, you get paladins, shadowknights, rangers and even the f*cking rogues to tank before you get a monk to do it.<br>
<br>
What this nerf looks like it will do is to make monks die faster when your FD fails when you pull. Up until now, if you're really quick, you survive if you're quick enough hitting /stonestance and mending when FD fails in order (or whatever panic-trick individual monks use) to get a second chance to FD when it pops again. Having a zillion AA points helps of course. But again - They Should!<br>
<br>
OK, I have to compare the nerfs a &quot;little&quot; although I feel classes should really speak for themselves. The status of monks today is a result of &quot;evolution&quot;. They are a considerable part of what monk-players see their class as. Wizards hardly see their characters as MB bitches (with occasional scale farming wiz-bitches known on Drinal as Saden and co.) and I actually think mages will be overjoyed that their damn stick won't force them into one very limited role. The CH nerf isn't really a nerf, like Nirtox pointed out. Mostly it will work as well as before for any cleric since only the very high end guilds can get a warrior above 7.5k HP (can they generally do that today even? How high is the top CiH warrior?). We will no doubt see a more effective CH spell anyway, and clerics will be the ones to get it.<br>
<br>
What other than pulling can a monk do? Yes, he can solo decently because he is not dead meat for sure if something goes wrong because he can feign, then back up, bandage or Fungi/Chestwrap/Mend heal himself or whatever and then come back and finish the mob he was fighting before he has managed to regenrate to any degree. This takes care of that IF the damage a monk takes comes faster than it did before (and that is really what VI says - We WILLtake more damage than before), because then the first round of the fight won't be long enough in order for him to gain the HP advantage with his healing options. Great job...<br>
<br>
Except if they ADJUST the dodge/parry chance we have. Lots of the happy posters above that don't really know a lot about monks seem to read something about an upgrade to those skills from the VI statement, but I didn't see anything to that effect (although VI kept the door open for the possibility if they find out that they are fucking us over). <br>
<br>
I repeat: Since when do monks tank? It will be interesting to see how this tweak fleshes out when it hits, but it doesn't look like a good one and will probably ruin our characters. Seriously, what monk, that has spent years in getting better equipment enabling him to take more beating and become better, wants to be bumped back to &quot;level-57ish-trying-to-solo-FG-shrooms&quot; status.<br>
<br>
I believe www.monkly-business.com speaks for what most monks are thinking right now:<br>
<br>
&quot;I have not seen any high level guilds using Monks as main Tanks for the simple reason that our damage is taken so randomly, where as a Defensive warrior can control and know his damage taken for 3 minutes, and if this is not enough, another Warrior takes his place. Where is there a spot for a monk in that setup?...as mentioned by many other Monks, with the few disciplines that we have which are actually worth using being defensive, what exactly did you (verant) have in mind for us? And more to the point, why bloody change your minds now?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uishmialmuaddib.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ishmial Muaddib</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Rtehsuq</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 8:28:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1466.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://212.212.159.252/tearaina/imagesP/Ishmial.jpg width=140 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
